#: ../../reading_habits.rst:5
msgid "Reading Habits"
msgstr "読書習慣"

#: ../../reading_habits.rst:7
msgid ""
"Omnivorous, but usually includes lots of science and science fiction. The "
"typical hacker household might subscribe to *Analog*\\, *Scientific "
"American*\\, *Whole-EarthReview*\\, and *Smithsonian* (most hackers ignore "
"*Wired* and other self-consciously ‘cyberpunk’ magazines, considering them "
":ref:`wannabee` fodder). Hackers often have a reading range that astonishes "
"liberal arts people but tend not to talk about it as much. Many hackers "
"spend as much of their spare time reading as the average American burns up "
"watching TV, and often keep shelves and shelves of well-thumbed books in "
"their homes."
msgstr ""
"雑食的だが、たいてい多くの科学と空想科学小説を含む。典型的なハッカー世帯は\\ *Analog*\\ 、\\ *Scientific "
"American*\\ 、\\ *Whole-EarthReview*\\ 、\\ *Smithsonian*\\ "
"を購読しているかもしれない(大半のハッカーは\\ *Wired*\\ や他の自意識過剰な‘サイバーパンク’雑誌を、\\ "
":ref:`wannabee`\\ "
"向けの餌とみなして無視する)。ハッカーはしばしば、リベラルアーツの人々を驚かせる読書範囲を持つが、それについてあまり話さない傾向がある。多くのハッカーは、平均的なアメリカ人がTVを見て費やすのと同じくらいの余暇を読書に費やし、しばしば読み込まれた本を家の棚に何段も並べている。"
